{
  "text": "All the ingredients in combination with 125 mg/L of nisin (Sigma Aldrich, England) were ground through a blender with a 5 mm plate (Gosonic, Turkey) for 4-5 min. Nisin solution, which was added to avoid the growth of Clostridium botulinum, was prepared by dissolving a required amount of nisin powder in sterilised 0.02N HCl solution. Burgers (25 g in weight, 50-60 mm in diameter, and 1 cm in thickness) were formed by a burger-maker according to [CITATION_1] . RSM (response surface methodology) was used to optimise the formulation. The results were analysed using Design Expert 6.0.2 software, and each of the dependent variables in the form of a quadratic regression model was presented as follows: ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "24842600"
